# Git Maintainer Workflow

Repository: https://github.com/CodeMaestroPro/Cyra-Tech-Enterprise-Website.git

After completing every development task:

1. Review the code for correctness.
2. Ensure the application builds successfully before committing whenever possible (`php artisan test`, `npm run build`).
3. Stage all changes: `git add .`
4. Generate a professional Conventional Commit message.
5. Commit: `git commit -m "<generated commit message>"`
6. Push to the current branch: `git push origin HEAD`

## Commit Rules

- Use Conventional Commits: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `style`, `chore`, `perf`, `test`, `ci`, `build`.
- Never use generic messages like "update" or "changes".
- Only commit when files have changed.
- Prefer scoped messages for modules, e.g. `feat(module-01): ...`.
